      "value": "<p><strong>Usage</strong> drawn on a shield</p><hr /><p>Similarity in the Dwarven words for \"wall\" and \"shield\" ensure that this angular rune, once used to shore up tunnels, can apply equally well in the heat of battle. A shield bearing this rune increases its circumstance bonus to AC by 1.</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-playtest-data.impossible-playtest-effects.Item.gBwMb0QqrBJVzyYc]{Effect: Holtrik, Rune of Dwarven Ramparts}</p><p><strong>Invocation</strong> You call the shield to its rightful place. You Raise the Shield bearing the rune, as if the rune-bearer had used Raise a Shield, and the shield retains the increased bonus to AC until the beginning of the creature's next turn.</p>"
